benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/allCustomFields - Retrieve account customFields

covered: Valid Request: Scenario @TC01 covers retrieval with only required accountId.
Empty Response: Scenario @TC06 covers case when no custom fields exist.
Query Parameters: Scenarios @TC02, @TC05, @TC07, @TC08, @TC09, @TC11, @TC13, @TC18, @TC31, @TC37, @TC38 cover various parameter filters and invalid inputs.
Error Handling: @TC12, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC16, @TC17, @TC19, @TC20, @TC22, @TC33, @TC34, @TC35, @TC36, @TC39 cover invalid accountId, service unavailability, and recovery scenarios.
Security: @TC14, @TC15, @TC17, @TC18 cover authentication, authorization, and injection attempts.
Performance: @TC11, @TC25, @TC26, @TC30, @TC29 cover large datasets, concurrency, and system load.
Regression & Compatibility: @TC21, @TC22 cover previous bug fixes and backward compatibility.
Edge Cases: @TC29, @TC30, @TC32, @TC33, @TC34, @TC35, @TC36, @TC37, @TC38 cover minimum/maximum values, invalid formats, and accessibility.
gaps: Pagination: No tests explicitly verify pagination or handling of large datasets beyond simple size assumptions.
Authorization: No explicit tests for unauthorized users or permission restrictions beyond missing/invalid tokens.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios testing system behavior under high request volume or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests checking for cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Timeouts & Retries: Limited coverage of network timeout handling, retries, or transient failures beyond @TC19 and @TC20.
Service Dependencies: No explicit tests for dependent service failures (e.g., audit service) beyond @TC23.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify correct handling of large datasets and response size limits.
Include tests for unauthorized access, permission restrictions, and role-based access control.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure system stability under load.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
Include tests for network timeouts, retries, and transient error recovery mechanisms.
Create tests for dependent service failures and fallback behaviors to improve robustness.
